<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="section-1a" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Function Definition</title>
  
  <p>A function definition always has the following parts: the word <alert>function</alert>, 
     the name of the function, a pair of parentheses, and a pair of curly brackets.
    The beginning and ending of a functon are marked with curly braces: an open curly brace {
    marks the beginning of the func?on, and a closed curly brace } marks the end of the 
    functon.</p> 
  <pre>
    <code>
      function nameOfFunction() {

      }
    </code>
  </pre>   

</section>